@Kaffie: @Geekless: without Tor support you lose Chinese users, a lot of M-E users, probably Russian users too. On top of that there's plenty of users who don't need Tor but still value the option of using it being there (eg. they are worried about the future state of internet freedom in their countries). Sure, when things get worse the other networks might start implementing anonymization, but being ahead of the rest on that front is definitely a plus.
.
@FraYoshi: True, comparing ZeroNet and IPFS is unfair to both as they solve different problems. I was thinking about Dat/Beaker for my comparison.
